# Plan: PulseBoard Channel Plugin

## Context

Add a new fictional "PulseBoard" channel plugin to OpenClaw. PulseBoard is an imaginary real-time bulletin board messaging platform where users post messages to named "boards" (group rooms) and can also send direct messages. The plugin must follow the same extension structure and SDK boundaries as existing bundled channel plugins (like Nostr for DMs or IRC for DM+group). No existing files may be modified — all new files go in `extensions/pulseboard/`.

---

## Reference Plugins

- **Nostr** (`extensions/nostr/`) — simple, single-account, DM-only. Primary template for structure.
- **IRC** (`extensions/irc/`) — multi-type (direct + group), used for group-chat adapter patterns.

---

## Key Design Decisions

| Concern | Decision |
|---|---|
| Config model | Single top-level account (`createTopLevelChannelConfigAdapter`), like Nostr |
| Auth | API key (`SecretInput`) |
| Chat types | `["direct", "group"]` |
| Text chunk limit | `4000` chars |
| DM inbound dispatch | `dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/direct-dm` |
| Group inbound dispatch | `dispatchInboundReplyWithBase` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/nextcloud-talk` (the only neutral public facade that re-exports this general-purpose helper) |
| DM policy default | `"pairing"` |
| Group policy default | `"allowlist"` |
| No external deps | Fictional platform — no real npm package needed |

---

## File Structure

All files under `extensions/pulseboard/`:

```
extensions/pulseboard/
├── openclaw.plugin.json        # Plugin manifest (id, channels, empty configSchema)
├── package.json                # npm metadata + openclaw config block
├── index.ts                    # defineChannelPluginEntry()
├── setup-entry.ts              # defineSetupPluginEntry()
├── api.ts                      # Public barrel (re-exports runtime-api)
├── runtime-api.ts              # Private runtime barrel (aggregates SDK subpaths)
└── src/
    ├── types.ts                # PulseBoardAccountConfig, ResolvedPulseBoardAccount, etc.
    ├── config-schema.ts        # Zod schema + buildChannelConfigSchema()
    ├── channel.ts              # createChatChannelPlugin() — main ChannelPlugin export
    ├── runtime.ts              # createPluginRuntimeStore()
    ├── client.ts               # Fictional PulseBoard API/WebSocket client stub
    ├── normalize.ts            # Target normalization (board names, user IDs)
    ├── monitor.ts              # Inbound message gateway loop
    ├── send.ts                 # Outbound message sender
    ├── setup-surface.ts        # ChannelSetupAdapter + ChannelSetupWizard
    └── channel.test.ts         # Vitest unit tests for plugin behavior
```

---

